{
  "texts": [
    "DNA fragments were received as dry residues in 96-well PCR plates in 2-4 μg quantities.",
    "These DNA samples were dissolved in 100 μL of doubledistilled H 2 O (ddH 2 O), yielding concentrations between 20-40 ng/μL.",
    "0.7 μL of these gene solutions were added to the wells of a 96-well PCR plate (Globe Scientific Inc., Mahwah, NJ).",
    "1.0 μL of an aqueous solution containing 60 ng/μL of linearized pET-22b(+) backbone with overhangs designed for Gibson ligation with the ordered DNA sequences was added to each of the wells of this plate.",
    "Finally, to each well was added 5 μL of Gibson assembly mix."
  ]
}